{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BASE CAMP - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A relief against the long harsh, hot day.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see lights on all over the camp, sounds of music, laughter from the barracks.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. UNDERWORLD HUTCH - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: King leads Chris down to a specially constructed cellar-like hutch dug deep into the ground on an isolated edge of the battalion perimeter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Ammo casing and canvas are piled over it, and sandbags surround it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: From the outside very little sound can be heard as they go down through a trap door made of ammo crates.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Past a lookout (Adams) pulling security, hitting a joint but alert.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: King motions to him, it's cool.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Inside is another world.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris looking around amazed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's like a private cabaret for the 'heads' who are there cooling out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Boxes of food from the States, beers, whiskey bottles, crates functioning as tables, hammocks hanging from poles, electric fans, tape decks, paraphenalia.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The boys are all dressed up in their Saturday night rags.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The clothes are clean, the headbands, the medallions are out, anything distinctive and individualistic.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the tapedeck, Jefferson Airplane's 'Go Ask Alice'.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: To Chris it is a new world.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And RHAH, the resident head, sitting there in all his finery puffing a huge burning red bowl in a three foot long Montagnard pipe, seems to be the lord of final judgement in this smoky underworld.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Across his naked chest, birds and snakes are tatooed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Around his neck a black skull and white ivory cross side by side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On his knuckles 'Love' and 'Hate' are tattooed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In his eyes, a dancing Satanic fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A poor rural Southern white, in his grizzled late 20's, he could be a Biker King.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Giving Chris the once-over.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH
{DIALOGUE}: Whatcha doing in the underworld Taylor?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KING
{META_DATA}: (smiling)
{DIALOGUE}: This ain't Taylor.
{DIALOGUE}: Taylor been shot.
{DIALOGUE}: This man Chris been resurrected ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris wondering what he's doing here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes roving over LERNER, CRAWFORD, MANNY, FLASH, FRANCIS, HOYT, TUBBS, DOC, other from the Platoon, about 9 or 10 of them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rhah eyes him back, hands him the bowl.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH
{DIALOGUE}: You lame Taylor?
