{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BARNES, Sgts.O'NEILL and WARREN, the quiet sullen black, SANDERSON and SAL play as ACE, the tiny radio kid, and MOREHOUSE look on; all of them drinking beer and bourbon chasers from a bottle.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WOLFE
{META_DATA}: (to O'Neill)
{DIALOGUE}: How's it going Red?
{META_DATA}: (using his nickname)
{CHARACTER_NAME}: O'NEILL
{DIALOGUE}: Shit, cocksucker's got all the cards tonight.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WOLFE
{META_DATA}: (to Barnes)
{DIALOGUE}: Looks like you're doing all right Sergeant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes, raking in the chips, is the big winner, a light bead of sweat on his forehead and a somewhat glassy look to the eye the only indication he is drunk - his shirt peeled off revealing a muscular, scarred body.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, and I ain't even cheating yet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SANDERSON
{META_DATA}: (the big blond kid)
{DIALOGUE}: Have some Kentucky windage Lieutenant.
{META_DATA}: (passes him the bottle of bourbon)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wolfe takes a nip.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES
{DIALOGUE}: Play Lieutenant?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WOLFE
{DIALOGUE}: Nah, I wouldn't want to get raped by you guys ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: O'NEILL
{DIALOGUE}: What are you saving up to be Lieutenant - Jewish?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Laughes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wolfe forces a smile, glad to move on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a continual worried rodent air about him, an anxiety, a desire to fill the vacuum in his leadership with a false masculinity.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WOLFE
{DIALOGUE}: Catch you men later.
{DIALOGUE}: Enjoy yourselves.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he goes, O'Neill shakes his head after him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: O'NEILL
{DIALOGUE}: Sorry ass motherfucker ain't he.
{DIALOGUE}: You think he gonna make it Barnes?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes plays a card, glances, a minute movement of his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: O'NEILL (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah that's what I figger.
{DIALOGUE}: Some dudes you jes' look in their faces and you KNOW they just ain't gonna make it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes looks - with some irony - at O'Neill.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Country Western tune has reached a crescendo whine which now mixes into:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. UNDERWORLD HUTCH - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Francis, the baby-faced black, and Manny, green shades covering his skinny face, lead with a high blues falsetto.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANCIS AND MANNY
{META_DATA}: (singing)
{DIALOGUE}: 'People say I'm the life of the party cause I tell a joke or two Although I may be laughing loud and hardy Deep inside I'm blue ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Hutch looks now like a Turkish bath with minimum visibility, the smoke fumes dense.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are all up dancing on their feet - King, Tubbs, Big Harold, Hoyt, Lerner, Crawford, Flash, Doc, Elias - a few light gestures with their hands above shoulder level, passing around the grass pipes while they shuffle, fingers clicking.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The song - Smokey Robinson's "Tracks of My Tears" - accompanies them from a vintage tapedeck.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ALL
{DIALOGUE}: '... Since you've left me, if you've seen me with another girl seeming like I'm having fun although she may be cute she's just a substitute because you're the permanent one ...'
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: King and Big Harold wave Chris into the Circle and he starts swaying with them, feeling as if he's being accepted into a new family.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rhah watches it all, puffing away on his magic dragon pipe, the shadows dancing on the walls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It looks like a Saturday night dance party.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A yearning for tenderness, for feminity, for a moment of peace in this nightmare life.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their eyes closed, thinking of dance partners that can't be here tonight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Singing their souls out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ALL (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: '... So take a good look at my face.
{DIALOGUE}: You'll see the smile looks out of place.
{DIALOGUE}: Look a little bit closer.
{DIALOGUE}: It's easy to trace.
{DIALOGUE}: The tracks of my tears...'
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. JUNGLE - NVA BUNKER COMPLEX - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An overwhelming 103 degree heat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris is once more on point, a little better now but obviously struggling with a thick unyielding bamboo thicket that forces him forward in a caveman crouch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Napalm jelly is hanging from the trees in great canopies of spider webs, obliterating the sky.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: New Year's Day, 1968.
{DIALOGUE}: Just another day.
{DIALOGUE}: Staying alive.
{DIALOGUE}: There's been a lot of movement neat the Cambodian border, regiments of NVA moving across.
{DIALOGUE}: A lot of little firefights, ambushes, we drop a lot of bombs, then we walk through the napalm like ghosts in a landscape ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris working his way over twisted, broken stumps, branches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the back of his flak jacket he's written, 'If I die bury me upside down so the whole world can kiss my ass'.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES
{DIALOGUE}: Pssst!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The signal for silence.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris freezes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes edging up to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (whispers)
{DIALOGUE}: Bunker ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: Where?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Doesn't see it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Following Barnes' imperceptible movement of his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bunker, dug into the ground and camouflaged with brush, is staring right at him, not more than 20 feet away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris is a dead man if ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes, checking the terrain, signals radioman Hoyt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes edging up to the bunker, eyes everywhere.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris following.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The tension builds.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They come up to the edge of it, peer in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nothing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes walks around it, slips in from back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris covers him, other guys coming up now, making a small perimeter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris now starts to see things he didn't see.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Right in front of his nose - there is a trench from this bunker to another and another.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is now in his view a complex of bunkers and thatched hootches and lean-tos all blending into the forest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A ghost city ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias and others fanning out now, careful ... whispered conversations in the wind.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris moves past a rope with freshly washed laundry stretching between two trees, clothes stirring in the wind.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks up as King points out a treehouse, then looks down as Lerner whispers something and points - NVA rucksacks are laid out on the ground in an orderly platoon-sized pattern.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. NVA BUNKER - TUNNEL POSITION - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias goes down into a dangerous-looking TUNNEL, on a rope with a .45.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes watching him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We sense Elias loves the danger, smiling.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NVA BUNKER - COMPLEX - MAIN POSITION - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lt. Wolfe signals Manny and Chris out onto the two flanks.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. NVA TREEHOUSE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rhah and King explore a treehouse.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rice stores.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rhah, an experienced soldier, seems tense, moves cautiously, expecting booby traps.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NVA BUNKER - WARREN'S POSITION - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sgt. Warren cautiously explores another bunker, probing a little tunnel in the bottom of it with a stick.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bunny, having a small frame, goes down into it, fearless.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NVA BUNKER - MANNY'S POSITION - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Manny, the skinny black boy with the coloured beads, is out on flank - alone, smoking a cigarette, humming.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NVA BUNKER - CHRIS' POSITION - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On the other flank, Chris, also alone, waits, listening to the sounds of the jungle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He too is smoking a cigarette.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The eeriness is everywhere.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rays of morning light peeking through the cathedral dome of the jungle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bird calls.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. NVA TUNNEL - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias climbs deeper and deeper into the hole, a rope attached to his waist leading out to the surface, his flashlight now coming around on a shaftway demarcating a TUNNEL that seems to stretch for at least 100 yards.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The light revealing cobwebs all along it, but tall enough for a small man.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. CHRIS' POSITION - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's quiet, weird.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris takes his pants down, squats.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He thinks he hears something, tenses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a soft rustling sound now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And as he focuses on it he realizes it is coming from very close to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Something light and sinuous moving over the leaves.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A bright yellow and orange-ringed krait viper is crawling right between his two legs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It stops, senses another life standing over it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris frozen with dread.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The snake crawls on, pulling its long, long 15 foot body behind it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: On Chris, eyes dilated, slowly regaining his breath looking around everywhere now.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. NVA TUNNEL - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias moving down the tunnel, fearless.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We expect something any moment to come out and nail him but nothing does.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stops.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His flashlight revealing a kitchen and an NVA hospital set up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A hammock swings as if someone just deserted it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In another hammock is a dead man.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias advances cautiously.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NVA BUNKER - COMPLEX - SANDERSON POSITION - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Spec 4 Sanderson, the big handsome blond kid, is moving through an abandoned bunker.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With him is Sal, a tough street kid with an intense face, all whiskered.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sanderson noticing now a metal box of 50-caliber ammo, U.S. marking, half-buried in the ground.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SANDERSON
{DIALOGUE}: Hey look at that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He opens the case.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Official-looking documents are inside, they glance through them, lighting cigarettes, the search over, successful, they relax.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SAL
{META_DATA}: (a worried type)
{DIALOGUE}: Leave it willya - it's gook shit.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SANDERSON
{DIALOGUE}: Nah this stuff's important.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He puts the documents back in the ammo case, lifts it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's the last thing he ever does.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NVA BUNKER - SANDERSON POSITION - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ensuing explosion shakes the ground, obliterating both boys, brances, smoke and dust flying out.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NVA BUNKER - CHRIS POSITION - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Out on flank, Chris hits the ground, hugs it.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NVA BUNKER - COMPLEX - SANDERSON POSTION - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes runs up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Black smoke sweeping through the trees.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sal suddenly appears, stepping out of the smoke, stunned.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The front of his body is soaked in blood from a thousand shrapnel holes, his clothes shredded, he stares at Barnes, dazed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Both his arms are gone and blood is geysering out like a water fountain.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He crumbles - dead or dying.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES
{DIALOGUE}: Corpsman!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He runs over to Sal, gets a hold of his face in a vicelike grip, enraged, tries to yell some sense into him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (directly to Sal)
{DIALOGUE}: Goddamit!
{DIALOGUE}: Are you fucking kids ever gonna learn!
{DIALOGUE}: Don't you understand how easy it is to die!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Doc running up - one look tells us all we need to know.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DOC
{DIALOGUE}: Holy Jesus!
