{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. NVA BUNKER - SANDERSON POSITION - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes is still there in the wrecked bunker, squatting there staring as if his mind has disconnected for a moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He reaches up, touches his scars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The look on his face suggests he is deeply wronged by this tragedy, that he is taking it very personally.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NVA BUNKER - MAIN POSITION - DAY
