{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias combing the ground for clues ... nothing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris looking on, can't believe it, none of them can, a collective chill running through the platoon.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. JUNGLE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Platoon moving downslope in the Jungle, their faces grim, quiet, deadly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: King is on point.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: We had to get to the village before dark so we left Elias with some men to keep looking and to wait for the engineers ... But it was King who found him ... about 1000 yards downriver, not far from the village - It was the end of the mystery.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A moving shot approaching Manny.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's trussed with rope, arms behind his back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Throat cut, eyes startled open, mouth shaped in a scream of terror.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes, the other men looking ... Chris.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes says it for everyone, 'The motherfuckers ...'
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VILLAGE - TRAIL - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They come up out of the jungle onto the side of a CART TRAIL, where a tiny village overlooks the river.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The VILLAGE is poor, a series of thatched hutches made of C-ration cardboard and aluminum beer can sidings, faint whiffs of smoke coming from cook fires.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pigs and dogs wander about.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An OLD VILLAGER watches them pass from his tillable plot, smoking a cigarette, one leg wrapped around his hoe, resting, no expression.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: ... the village, which had stood for maybe a thousand years, didn't know we were coming that day.
{DIALOGUE}: If they had they would have run ... Barnes was at the eye of our rage - and through him, our Captain Ahab - we would set things right again.
{DIALOGUE}: That day we loved him ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A pig loiters along the trail, rooting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bunny coming up on it with a smile.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUNNY
{DIALOGUE}: Hey pig, pig - come here, pig, pig.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The pig grunts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bunny leveling his shotgun, fires point blank.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A horrible squeal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris, directly behind him, looks disgusted.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VILLAGE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tony suddenly points, excited, calls to Barnes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TONY
{DIALOGUE}: There goes one!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their POV - a young VILLAGER fleeing down the slope.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes doesn't hesitate, nails him with a short volley of well- placed shots.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES
{META_DATA}: (to Tony)
{DIALOGUE}: Check him out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns back into the village.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VILLAGE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Troops fanning out over the village, some TWO DOZEN VILLAGERS scattering to collect their children, dogs barking.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SGTS.O'NEIL AND WARREN
{DIALOGUE}: Get em out!
{DIALOGUE}: Get em out!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VILLAGE TUNNEL - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In another part of the village, Barnes hovers over a hole leading into some kind of tunnel.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES
{DIALOGUE}: Get out of there you fuckheads move!
{DIALOGUE}: Move!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fires a warning shot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Three VILLAGERS climbing out of the spider hole, arms raised, but not showing any emotion.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes turning to his radioman Hoyt and Big Harold accompanying.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (to Harold)
{DIALOGUE}: Put'em in the pig pen.
{META_DATA}: (to Hoyt)
{DIALOGUE}: There's more down there.
{DIALOGUE}: Gimme your Willy Pete.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hoyt, with reluctance in his eyes, hands over a specially shaped grenade.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes stands over the hole, the grenade in hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The three VILLAGERS who just came out of the hole, yell from the distance, to others still in the tunnel, pleading with them to come out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: FIRE IN THE HOLE!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes throws the phosphorus in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A muted EXPLOSION.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then sizzling acidic fumes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frying sounds.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A hideous scream from somewhere deep in the hole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hoyt, watching, is sickened.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes businesslike.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Villagers, in grief, howl and tear at their faces.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FU SHENG
{META_DATA}: (hustling up to Barnes)
{DIALOGUE}: Sarge, we found some shit!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes going with him.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VILLAGE - OUTSIDE HUTCH - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sun is sittin there hot and high in the sky.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris, strangling in heat, a demented look on his face, staggers into a hutch with Francis.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT. HUTCH - VILLAGE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Threadbare, poor, a typical Buddhist shrine in the corner, motes of light crisscross through the poor matting and c-ration sides.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris edges over, pries up a floorboard, flips it over, scared.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's a tunnel inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A long dark dangerous hole.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: La Dai!
{DIALOGUE}: La Dai!
{DIALOGUE}: GET THE FUCK OUTTA THERE!
