{DIALOGUE}: Yeah - stoned's the way to be ...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VILLAGE - DITCH - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In a ditch running alongside the Village, partially concealed by foliage and anthills, Tony, Morehouse, and the ubiquitous Bunny have a 12-YEAR-OLD VIETNAMESE GIRL pinned to the ground, gagged and squirming, naked.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are fucking her to death.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Junior looks on, both curious and disgusted, but doesn't take part.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TONY
{DIALOGUE}: Take her up the ass ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As they roll her over, like excited dogs in heat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris, coming up, sees their heads dipping up and down on the other side of the anthill, knows what they're doing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He makes a conscious decision to do something.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He runs over.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: LET HER GO!
{DIALOGUE}: YOU HEAR ME!
{DIALOGUE}: YOU ASSHOLE!
{DIALOGUE}: LET HER GO!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He strides right into them, shoves them off hard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The girl is in tears.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TONY
{DIALOGUE}: What the fuck you want - she's a dink.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: NO - YOU STUPID FUCK ... DON'T ... DON'T ... YOU TOO BUNNY.
{DIALOGUE}: MOREHOUSE.
{DIALOGUE}: OFF!
{DIALOGUE}: NO!
{DIALOGUE}: DON'T ... DON'T!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He seems disconnected, dazed by the sun, like he's talking to dogs - loud, repetitive words coming out of an anger he can barely control, trying to restore some sanity to a world gone totally nuts today.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Don't they understand?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Don'tthey have any sense of a mind?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Any kind of decency?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Men looking at him as if he's the one who's gone nuts, not them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bunny looking at Morehouse looking at Tony looking at Junior.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The irony is lost on them, as Chris pushes through to help the poor girl put her scanty clothes back on.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (to the girl)
{DIALOGUE}: It's okay ... it's okay ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias appears behind Bunny and the others, sees what's happened.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He signals them to move out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELIAS
{DIALOGUE}: Get outta here.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The men grumble and slink off quietly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias watching as...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris helps her to her feet, wounded in the intestines, she can barely stand, blood saoking in her nether regions.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris slings her up as gently as he can and carries her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{META_DATA}: (as if to himself)
{DIALOGUE}: It's okay, it's okay ...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VILLAGE - PIG PEN - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Near the pig pen, a DOZEN SUSPECTS are being led away on ropes by Tubbs, Warren, Rodriguez.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The others left behind look back at their village in ruins, homes burning, livestock dead or scattered, belongings thrown and broken in the dirt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BABIES wail, the adults squat there on their heels watching with absolutely no trace of outward emotion.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Past this Bosch-like canvas, Chris - carrying the girl - walks dazed by the horrors of this long afternoon.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. VILLAGE TRAIL - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The soldiers depart the village.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A huge EXPLOSION now rocks the earth and sends a spray of smoke into the blue sky as the weapons cache explodes in stages that sound like the end of the world.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. PERIMETER #2 - JUNGLE - LATE AFTERNOON DUSK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Company is digging into another overnight perimeter on a ridge with a view of the Valley where the Village was.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: C-Ration fires all around the perimeter.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. COMPANY CP - DUSK -- MORNING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At the Company,l Elias, Captain Harris, Barnes, Lt.Wolfe are huddled.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Close on Harris, looking from face to face, assuming a judicial attitude.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAPTAIN HARRIS
{DIALOGUE}: ... and you Lieutenant?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LIEUTENANT WOLFE
{DIALOGUE}: I didn't see anything sir.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELIAS
{DIALOGUE}: I did.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LIEUTENANT WOLFE
{DIALOGUE}: That dink was reported to me as NVA sir by Sergeant Barnes.
{DIALOGUE}: Sergeant Barnes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Squirreling out of any responsibility.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELIAS
{DIALOGUE}: My report sir, will include Lt.Wolfe as being witness to the shooting ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CAPTAIN HARRIS
{DIALOGUE}: All right, Elias.
{DIALOGUE}: Sergeant Barnes, I want a report from you ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES
{DIALOGUE}: You got it sir - and I can throw in plenty of eye- witnesses if you want sir ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HARRIS
{DIALOGUE}: Not now.
{DIALOGUE}: We'll get into this when we get back to base camp.
{DIALOGUE}: Right now I need every man in the field, I want your guys to stick together ... Elias?
{DIALOGUE}: Barnes?
{DIALOGUE}: ... You hear me?
{DIALOGUE}: This is no time for fighting with each other.
{META_DATA}: (pause, they nod)
{DIALOGUE}: Tomorrow we're going back into that bunker complex - from the East.
{META_DATA}: (continuing)
{DIALOGUE}: First Platoon will lead ... Brigade thinks they might be back there tomorrow.
{DIALOGUE}: That's all ... Get some rest.
{META_DATA}: (turns away)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes, Elias eye each other and move off.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. PERIMETER #2 - DUSK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wolfe walks alongside Barnes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WOLFE
{DIALOGUE}: Don't worry about it Sergeant, he won't be able to prove a thing, he's a troublemaker but ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes is obviously worried, although he doesn't let on.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES
{DIALOGUE}: Elias' a waterwalker ... like them politicians in Washington.
{DIALOGUE}: Want to fight their war with one hand tied round their balls.
{DIALOGUE}: Ain't no time or need for a courtroom out here ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wolfe leaves him as Barnes turns into his foxhole where Bunny and O'Neill await him anxiously.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: O'NEILL
{DIALOGUE}: How'd it go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Banres shrugs.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUNNY
{DIALOGUE}: Thataway Sarge, fuckin' Elias man, fuckin' squeal that's what he is, gonna get everybody in the platoon in shit.
{DIALOGUE}: Somebody oughta fix his ass ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes fixing his coffee.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: O'NEILL
{META_DATA}: (worried)
{DIALOGUE}: Gonna be an investigation or something Bob?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes says nothing, a cryptic look.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: O'Neill worried, Bunny, taking his cue from Barnes, slaps him on the back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BUNNY
{DIALOGUE}: Ya worry too much O'Neill ...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. PERIMETER #2 - CHRIS' POSITION - DUSK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elsewhere on the perimeter, Chris is digging out a foxhole with Rhah, as King and Lerner prepare the C's for dinner.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH
{DIALOGUE}: I know Barnes six months and I'll tell ya something - that man is MEAN, red in his soul like a dick on a dog.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KING
{DIALOGUE}: Barnes gets killed, his jaws'd go on clacking ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: Where's he form?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH
{DIALOGUE}: Barnes comes from Hell.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LERNER
{DIALOGUE}: Tennessee someplace.
{DIALOGUE}: Hill country.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH
{DIALOGUE}: Barnes took a bullet right there.
{DIALOGUE}: At Ia Drang Valley
{META_DATA}: ... (points to his forehead)
{DIALOGUE}: And the cocksucker SURVIVED - that's BAAAD man.
{DIALOGUE}: That's his high, baby.
{DIALOGUE}: High on WAR!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes flare out dramamtically.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris, enthralled in spite of himself.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KING
{DIALOGUE}: He done a year in Japan in the hospital, then when he gets out, the first thing he done is re-up.
{DIALOGUE}: Four years he been in the field ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH
{DIALOGUE}: ... and you know how many times he done been shot?
{META_DATA}: (Chris shakes his head)
{DIALOGUE}: Seven times!
{META_DATA}: (with his fingers)
{DIALOGUE}: Seven.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: And he still wanted to come back?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LERNER
{DIALOGUE}: Does a pee wee wanna take a wee wee?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH
{DIALOGUE}: The Good Lord works his revenge in strange ways.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KING
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, you done said it.
{DIALOGUE}: Revenge on US.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: Does he have a metal plate in his head?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH
{META_DATA}: (smiles)
{DIALOGUE}: You mean he's crazy?
{DIALOGUE}: No more crazy'n the rest of us been out in the bush too long.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LERNER
{DIALOGUE}: Well he ain't normal that's fosure.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH
{DIALOGUE}: That's what he is ... Baaaa!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His hand flashes forward in front of Chris.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 'HATE' is written across the left hand knuckles in a sloppy, purplish-black tatoo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris looking at it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: ... and he's FILLED with it.
{DIALOGUE}: He's roaming these jungles looking for little yellow devils to kill.
{DIALOGUE}: Remember the Devil does God's work too.
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: ... and this here's Elias ... Baaaa!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The other knuckle is out - 'LOVE' tattooed across it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rhah smiles his crazy smil.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris stares fascinated at the two knuckles side by side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A moment on his face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KING
{DIALOGUE}: Love, yeah!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LERNER
{META_DATA}: (makes a cuckoo sign)
{DIALOGUE}: Here we go again with the crazy preacher stuff.
{DIALOGUE}: Rhah seen too many movies.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH
{DIALOGUE}: Baaa, got no time to go to the movies.
{DIALOGUE}: Love and Hate too busy fighting for possession of my soul.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: Where's Elias come from?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH
{META_DATA}: (interjecting)
{DIALOGUE}: 'Lias come naturally.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LERNER
{DIALOGUE}: ... don't know.
{DIALOGUE}: Done some time.
{DIALOGUE}: Heard he worked the oil wells in Oklahoma, made some bread and washed up in El Lay.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KING
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, get married to some crazy El Lay bitch, an actress or somethin', she blew all his bread - LSD, gurus, all that California shit, and then she turns him into the cops on a drug rap.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH
{DIALOGUE}: Not the only man to meet his Jezebel either.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KING
{DIALOGUE}: So he got a reduced and come over here.
{DIALOGUE}: Nam's his freedom man, Nam's his pussy.
{DIALOGUE}: Three years he been here.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: Three years, Jesus, he's crazy as Barnes ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KING
{DIALOGUE}: Well sometimes a man jes don' wanna go back.
{DIALOGUE}: How you gonna talk to civilians man?
{DIALOGUE}: People back in the world just don't give a shit, y'know what I mean, to them you're a fuckin' animal is all -
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LERNER
{META_DATA}: (to Chris)
{DIALOGUE}: I was home on leave y'know and everybody's just worried 'bout making money, everybody's out for themselves, they don't even want to talk about it man, it's like the fucking Twilight Zone back there - you wouldn't even KNOW there's a war on here.
{DIALOGUE}: My sister says to me why you have to go there like I started this ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH
{DIALOGUE}: Baaaa!
{DIALOGUE}: Fuck it, they sold us out - so what!
{DIALOGUE}: What'd you'all expect?
{DIALOGUE}: Civilian life is phoney BULLSHIT man.
{DIALOGUE}: They're ROBOTS man - watchin' dopey television and drivin' dopey cars, and they fuck up, nobody dies.
{DIALOGUE}: That's all right, you keep fuckin' up, politicians keep lyin'.
{DIALOGUE}: Cause it don't really matter.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't mean shit.
{DIALOGUE}: So what!
{DIALOGUE}: Whatcha want - a parade!
{DIALOGUE}: Fuck that too!
{DIALOGUE}: No war time no grunt never got no respect.
{DIALOGUE}: Till he was dead - and even THEN!
{DIALOGUE}: You're fighting for YOURSELF man!
{DIALOGUE}: You're fighting for your SOUL, dat's all.
{DIALOGUE}: Remember dat.
{DIALOGUE}: And it's some goddamn battle too - if you'se a man, wrestle with that angel ...
{META_DATA}: (swings his entrenching tool in a rhythmic chain-gang style)
{DIALOGUE}: ... Love and Hate - the whole shitbang show, that's the story then and now and it ain't hardly gonna change ...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. PERIMETER #2 - JUNGLE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The stars are out in magnificent splendor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A breeze rustling through the trees.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. PERIMETER #2 - CHRIS' POSITION - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris is turning in his sleep, perturbed, writhing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The whispering is more and more urgent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Death is all around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He shoots up out of his poncho liner as if shot, stunned.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Scared.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looks around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All is quiet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Men sleeping.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias is huddled in his poncho on guard next to his foxhole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris joins him, sitting, wiping the sleep from his eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: ... I can't sleep, why don't you get some sack time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELIAS
{DIALOGUE}: ... don't feel like it either.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: ... beautiful night.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELIAS
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah.
{DIALOGUE}: I love this place at night.
{DIALOGUE}: The stars ... there's no right or wrong in them, they're just there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: That's a nice way of putting it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias cuffs a joint, keeping its glow hidden in the dark.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A pause, both of them meditative.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Barnes got it in for you, don't he?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELIAS
{META_DATA}: (philosophically)
{DIALOGUE}: Barnes believes in what he's doing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: And you, do you believe?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELIAS
{DIALOGUE}: In '65 - yeah.
{DIALOGUE}: Now ...
{META_DATA}: (pause)
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: What happened today's just the beginning.
{DIALOGUE}: We're gonna lose this war ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{META_DATA}: (surprised)
{DIALOGUE}: You really think so ... us?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias' eyes seem to go to some inner place, his passion surging.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELIAS
{DIALOGUE}: ... we been kicking other people's asses so long I guess it's time we got our own kicked.
{DIALOGUE}: The only decent thing I can see coming out of here are the survivors - hundreds of thousands of guys like you Taylor going back to every little town in the country knowing something about what it's like to take a life and what that can do to a person's soul - twist it like Barnes and Bunny and make 'em sick inside and if you got any brains you gonna fight it the rest of your life cause it's cheap, killing is cheap, the cheapest thing I know and when some drunk like O'Neill starts glorifying it, you're gonna puke all over him and when the politicians start selling you a used war all over again, you and your generation gonna say go fuck yourself 'cause you know, you've seen it, and when you know it, deep down there ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He plants his fist in Chris' gut, expelling his breath such is the force of the blow - like a power passed between them.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELIAS (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: ... you know it till you die ... that's why the survivors remember.
{DIALOGUE}: 'Cause the dead don't let em forget.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes blazing, reliving the deaths in the village, licking the wounds for the platoon, mourning the failure of its heroism.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris looking at him, a little awed by his intensity.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias looks away, embarrassed that he has sermonized, looks back at the stars.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELIAS (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh shit!
{DIALOGUE}: Sometimes there's things in my head ... man.
{DIALOGUE}: Grass does that to me, fucks me all up like a crazy Indian ...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: Do you believe that stuff about ... knowing you're gonna die?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELIAS
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, those are the guys that live.
{DIALOGUE}: I really don't think Death gives a shit, it's like a giant garbage can, I think it takes whatever it can get ... you never know where it's gonna come from anyway ... so why spin your wheels?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He shrugs, a certain bravado masking his own uncertainty.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: ... You ever think about reincarnation, all that stuff?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A lightning quick movement follows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias' hand passing over his face like a mime, a click of the fingers and he leans closer to Chris.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A new expression on his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Devil's eyes, mocking child, danger in his soul, excitement, sex - the Elias that Chris saw in the smoking session in base camp.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris smiles, sucked in, almost laughs and then the face is gone again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELIAS
{DIALOGUE}: Sure, goes on all the time.
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe a piece of me's in you now, who knows.
{DIALOGUE}: But when you die - really die - that's a big return ticket.
{META_DATA}: (soft)
{DIALOGUE}: I like to think I'm gonna come back as ... as wind or fire - or a deer
{META_DATA}: (likes the image)
{DIALOGUE}: ... yeah, a deer ...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He smiles at the thought.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris looks at him, looks away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A shooting star falls suddenly and dryly through the cosmos.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their eyes.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. JUNGLE - STREAM - DAY (RAIN)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Platoon moves along a shallow STREAM bordering the jungle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A thick RAIN falls amid cracks of distant thunder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris, Rhah, Francis, Big Harold, others are at the rear of the platoon, their ponchos pulled over them like big sad grey tents.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's a holdup ahead and the Men rest on rocks or stand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The rain makes a pointilistic pattern, the men collages of grey, their rifles slung upside down to keep dry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes is up ahead, out of the stream bank, on the radio.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. JUNGLE CHURCH - DAY (RAIN)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lerner's on point, resting in the shadow of a decaying old French Catholic Church from the 19th Century.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The jungle has long ago won the battle, vines creeping into the cracks, remnants of arches layered around the church at the epicenter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind Lerner is Sgt.Warren and his radioman.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. JUNGLE CLEARING - DAY (RAIN)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias, further back, is checking out the jungle alongside the clearing, noticing a number of old spider holes long since abandoned.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He goes over and checks them.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. JUNGLE - STREAM - DAY (RAIN)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Back at the stream, Rhah, looking old and whiskered under his poncho hood, lights up a roach, puffs it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another crack of thunder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris comes over, sits with him on his rock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rhah passes him the joint.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He smokes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Big Harold pulls a leech out of his open crotch area.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HAROLD
{DIALOGUE}: Shit, lookit this little fucker trying to get up ma glory hole.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANCIS
{DIALOGUE}: Hey Big Harold, put dat in your turkey loaf it won't come out your back end.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KING
{META_DATA}: (ribbing)
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, big boy, thought you had that laundry gig all laid out?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BIG HAROLD
{META_DATA}: (pissed)
{DIALOGUE}: Shit, got to paint myself white get one of dem jobs.
{DIALOGUE}: Get ma request in for a circumcision.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KING
{DIALOGUE}: Gonna be a rabbi man?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FRANCIS
{DIALOGUE}: Gonna cut your pecker down to size hunh Big Harold?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BIG HAROLD
{DIALOGUE}: Dat's okay wid me, better to have a small one den no one at all.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: KING
