{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: I'll go with you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: ELIAS
{DIALOGUE}: No ... I move faster alone.
{META_DATA}: (a grin)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias, his pack stripped, is gone, like a fleet leaf, vanishing into the Jungle.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH
{META_DATA}: (stringing them out)
{DIALOGUE}: Okay Crawford - over here.
{DIALOGUE}: Taylor - down twenty yards behind that tree.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. JUNGLE - WOLFE'S POSITION - DAY (MIST)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes has finished correcting the fire mission, hurls the handset back at Wolfe, a wild look in his eyes, studying the incoming fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Makes a decision.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES
{DIALOGUE}: Let's move back, link up with Three.
{DIALOGUE}: Let the arty do a little work.
