{DIALOGUE}: We pull back they'll be cut off.
{DIALOGUE}: He needs cover fire.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES
{META_DATA}: (looks at him like he's stupid)
{DIALOGUE}: I'll get him.
{META_DATA}: (with a threatening undertone)
{DIALOGUE}: You just haul ass too lootenant.
{META_DATA}: (going, to Ace)
{DIALOGUE}: ... don't send Bravo Three up till I get back to the CP.
{DIALOGUE}: Now move out, all of you.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As he snaps his weapon onto full auto and runs off after Elias in a crouch ... a man with a mission.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. JUNGLE - RHAH AND CHRIS' POSITION - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Next to the Church deployed in the jungle, Rhah looks on, silent.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris in his position, waits.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is so silent in comparison to the racket from the battle across the forest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Mist clings to the trees, moist and lovely.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then, a flicker of movement, sound.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris hears it, tightens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His POV - at fifty yards.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An evanescence of beige and green uniforms moving towards him very fast, scurrying.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They look like headless ghosts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris opens fire.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{DIALOGUE}: GET EM!!!!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rhah and Crawford open up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A rachet of sound, one of the fiures seems to go down, then another but at this distance through jungle it is difficult to say.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The firing just as suddenly breaks off and the silence returns.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS (CONT'D)
{META_DATA}: (ecstatic)
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah!
{DIALOGUE}: I got two of them fuckers ...
