{DIALOGUE}: NOW.
{DIALOGUE}: Or I'll Article 15 both your asses.
{DIALOGUE}: Move!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris and Rhah look at Barnes sullenly, then reluctantly start moving Crawford onto a poncho liner they use as a litter.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES (CONT'D)
{DIALOGUE}: Move it, MOVE IT!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's in his blackest rage, the force of his words almost physically pushing the men to move out with Crawford.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes turns now to deal with Elias.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ELIAS' JUNGLE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elsewhere, Elias stands silently, listens to the forest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the distance the firefight can hardly be heard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His helmet gone, his hair hanging free, he is at his best now - alone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hears it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Somebody running through the jungle, about 100 yards, boots on leaves, coming towards him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He begins to move lateral to the sound.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His steps unheard, better at this than the enemy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THREE ENEMY FIGURES now appear, crouched and moving very fast with light equipment through the mist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias swerves up in immediate foreground, his back to us, FIRING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All three Figures fall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A quick glimpse of Elias, not bothering to stop, moving to his next position.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BARNES' JUNGLE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes, moving through the jungle, reacts to the fire, resetting his course.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Like a hunter stalking a deer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Suddenly there's more firing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then silence -
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ELIAS' JUNGLE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TWO MORE ENEMY lie dead in the jungle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A rustle of movement, then a CRY - chilling, jubilant, a war cry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A pair of feet moving lightly over the jungle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A glimpse of Elias.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In his full glory.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Roaming the jungle, born to it.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. BARNES' JUNGLE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes fixing on him, moving.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ELIAS' JUNGLE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An NVA SOLDIER, jungle-whiskered, dirty, smart, crouches, listens, looks to his PARTNER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: What are they fighting here?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The First One mutter something sharp and they split fast in the direction they've come.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They get about six steps when Elias suddenly rises up from the bush, not ten yards in front of them, his shots ripping into them, driving the surprised life from them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias is gone.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. NVA JUNGLE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elsewhere, another three NVA stop, turn and flee back from where they came.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. JUNGLE CHURCH - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris and Rhah get Crawford back to the church grounds, lay him down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No activity around them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris plunges back into the jungle where they left Barnes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: RHAH
{DIALOGUE}: Taylor!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. ELIAS AND BARNES' JUNGLE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes moving, stops, listens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Something is running towards him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But it's hidden by the bush.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He brings his rifle up smooth and quick, waits, then as the bush parts, Elias is standing there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looking at Barnes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes sees him, starts to lower his rifle, but then stops.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He raises it back an inch, sights it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pause.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A cold searing look of hatred coming over his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In that moment, Elias understands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Quick as a deer, he makes his move, trying to plunge back into the bush.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes fires.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Once, twice, three times - the blast rocking the jungle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias jerking backwards into the bush, mortally wounded.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bird cries.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A crime against nature.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes calmly lowers his rifle, and walks away from it.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. CHRIS' JUNGLE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris, cutting through the jungle, hears the shots.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stops, listens.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Someone is moving through bush towards him, leaves and foliage shaking.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris tightens, raises his rifle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes steps through into his sight - sees him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris lowers his rifle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes walking past him as if he weren't even there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES
{DIALOGUE}: Elias is dead.
{DIALOGUE}: Join up with the platoon.
{DIALOGUE}: Move it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: CHRIS
{META_DATA}: (shocked)
{DIALOGUE}: He's dead!
{DIALOGUE}: Where?
{DIALOGUE}: ... You saw him?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BARNES
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah.
{DIALOGUE}: Back about 100 metres.
{DIALOGUE}: He's dead, now get going, the gooks are all over the fuckin' place.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Moving on quickly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris has no choice but to follow, looking back one more time.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. CHURCH GROUNDS - JUNGLE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TWO CHOPPERS are coming into a LZ in front of the Church.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two platoons, Second and Third, reinforcing, are being evacuated as quickly as possible, one load (6-8 men, depending on the wounded) after other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The choppers are spraying dust all over the place.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A scene of chaos, radio talk layering it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Doc is out of supplies, making do with improvised bandages, etc.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WOLFE
{DIALOGUE}: MOVE IT MOVE IT MOVE IT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lerner goes by, horribly wounded on a makeshift litter, into the chopper, Doc attending, holding the IV.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris catching a glimpse of him, waiting to get on the chopper, turning to look as:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hoyt and Sgt.Warren, both wounded, are hurried aboard on litters.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The chopper lifting off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris and others now running to the corpses of Flash, Morehouse, and Fu Sheng lying under dirty ponchos, their boots sticking out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The ponchos are blown away in a burst of wind off the chopper blades, revealing their faces - dirt stuffing their eyes and mouths, waxen figures.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris and the others lifting them and carrying them towards the next chopper now coming in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They throw the bodies on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tubbs and Crawford, both wounded, now move past Chris, into the chopper.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris running back, with King carrying a litter - their eyes falling on:
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes talking with Wolfe and Ace, making signals under the roaring sounds of the chopper.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shaking his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No Elias.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris and King looking at each other, mute.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They numbly start loading Big Harold, minus his leg, onto the stretcher.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Third Chopper is down now, waiting, roaring blades silhouetting off the face of the cathedral.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A ROCKET BLAST suddenly goes off not too far from the chopper, incoming fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The DOOR GUNNER signaling for them to hurry, laying out fire.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: INT/EXT. CHOPPER - JUNGLE - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris and King hustling Big Harold's 250 pounds into the chopper.
