{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: So's the Door Gunner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias is coming out of the jungle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Staggering, blood disfiguring his face and chest, hanging on with all his dimming strength, looking up at them - trying to reach them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris shakes Wolfe, his words drowned out by the roar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Chopper Captain looking down, dips.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His co-pilot pointing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The NVA are coming out of the jungle, closing on the spot where Elias is.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Incoming rounds are hitting the chopper.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Door Gunner maniacally firing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes looking down at the man, can't believe it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias is on his last legs now, obviously being hit by the incoming fire of the NVA.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He falls to his knees, still stretching upwards for life.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Chopper Captain shakes his head at Wolfe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Chopper dips one more time firing at the NVA, low and fierce over the jungle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris looking back in horror.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias crucified.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The NVA coming out now by the dozens from the treeline.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Elias crumbling to the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Obviously dead or dying.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: HELICAPTAIN ON RADIO
{DIALOGUE}: ... we still got one on the deck.
{DIALOGUE}: Bring the gunships in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes drawing in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Chris looking at him in revulsion.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He knows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Barnes sees his look, ignores it, all of them sitting there silent, living with that final horrifying image of Elias.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. UNDERGROUND HUTCH - BASE CAMP - NIGHT
